      "name": "Note: Escalate Failure to Microsoft Teams"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Distill documents with Notion and Microsoft Teams for your team\n\n**Pattern:** AI Summarize & Route · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nDistill documents with Notion and Microsoft Teams for your team. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual drip campaigns is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Collect Raw Text → Extract Structured Fields → All Required Fields Found? → Upsert into Notion → Merge Review Paths → Cap Batch Volume → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ai summarize & route without manual effort\n- Anyone automating drip campaigns in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Groq API key; Microsoft OAuth2; Notion integration token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "7a670282-3a30-93c6-398f-d294d463c453",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "f3b6a273-fde4-989d-bc38-74b849fcbfc7",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "1d2e6126-1cce-d1cc-181a-b45902aabdb6",
      "name": "🔐 Security"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        610,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "2627cc19-9b42-c471-eca0-f5d7670b6de7",
      "name": "🤖 AI cluster"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your drip campaigns process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
